### MedhaShaala API Test Requests

# Base URL
@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8000

### 1. Register a new user with email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/users/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "securepassword123",
    "re_password": "securepassword123",
    "role": "user",
    "subscription_plan": "base"
}

### 2. Register a new user with phone
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/users/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Jane Smith",
    "phone": "+1234567890",
    "password": "securepassword123",
    "re_password": "securepassword123",
    "role": "user",
    "subscription_plan": "standard"
}

### 3. Register a new user with both email and phone
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/users/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Bob Wilson",
    "email": "bob@example.com",
    "phone": "+0987654321",
    "password": "securepassword123",
    "re_password": "securepassword123",
    "role": "admin",
    "subscription_plan": "premium"
}

### 4. Login with email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/jwt/create/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "securepassword123"
}

### 5. Login with phone
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/jwt/create/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone": "+1234567890",
    "password": "securepassword123"
}

### 6. Get user profile (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/users/me/
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 7. Update user profile
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/users/me/
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Updated Doe",
    "subscription_plan": "premium"
}

### 8. Refresh JWT token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/jwt/refresh/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "refresh": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 9. Verify JWT token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/jwt/verify/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "token": "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 10. Request password reset
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/users/reset_password/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john@example.com"
}

### 11. Get API schema
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/schema/

### 12. Access Swagger documentation
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/docs/

### 13. Access ReDoc documentation
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/redoc/

### 14. Admin panel
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/
